{"name": "lanscape", "metadata": {"name": "lanscape", "version": "1.2.4", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["flask", "psutil", "pywebview", "requests", "scapy", "setuptools", "tabulate"], "summary": "A python based local network scanner", "upload_time": 1729191289}, "documentation": ["# LANscape\nA python based local network scanner.\n\n![screenshot](https://github.com/mdennis281/py-lanscape/raw/main/src/lanscape/static/img/readme1.png)\n\n## Local Run\n```sh\npip install lanscape\npython -m lanscape\n```\n\n## Flags\n - `--port <port number>` port of the flask app (default: 5001)\n - `--nogui` run in web mode (default: false)\n - `--reloader` essentially flask debug mode- good for local development (default: false)\n - `--logfile` save log output to lanscape.log\n - `--loglevel <level>` set the logger's log level (default: INFO)\n - `--headless` similar to nogui but doesnt try to open a browser (default: false)\n \n\nExamples:\n```shell\npython -m lanscape --reloader\npython -m lanscape --nogui --port 5002\npython -m lanscape --logfile --loglevel DEBUG\n```\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### MAC Address / Manufacturer is inaccurate/unknown\nThe program does an ARP lookup to determine the MAC address. This lookup\ncan sometimes require admin-level permissions to retrieve accurate results.\n*Try elevating your shell before execution.*\n\n### Message \"WARNING: No libpcap provider available ! pcap won't be used\"\nThis is a missing dependency related to the ARP lookup. This is handled in the code, but you would get marginally faster/better results with this installed: [npcap download](https://npcap.com/#download)\n\n\n### Unable to start webview client. Try --nogui (Linux)\nLinux and QT (GUI package) dont seem to play well with each other very well. If you really want the gui (`python -m lanscape --nogui` is almost as good) I had success on ubuntu desktop by running these:\n```sh\nsudo apt install libcairo2-dev libxt-dev libgirepository1.0-dev\npip install pycairo PyGObject qtpy PyQt5 PyQtWebEngine\n```\n\n\n### Something else\nFeel free to submit a github issue detailing your experience.\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "lanscape.blueprints", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "lanscape.blueprints.scan_manager", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "lanscape.blueprints.log", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "lanscape.blueprints.ScanManager", "xref": {"fqname": "lanscape.libraries.subnet_scan.ScanManager", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "lanscape.blueprints.api", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "lanscape.blueprints.api.api_bp", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "lanscape.blueprints.api.Blueprint", "xref": {"fqname": "flask.Blueprint", "project": "flask"}}, {"name": "lanscape.blueprints.api.port", "xref": {"fqname": "lanscape.blueprints.api..port", "project": null}}, {"name": "lanscape.blueprints.api.scan", "xref": {"fqname": "lanscape.blueprints.api..scan", "project": null}}, {"name": "lanscape.blueprints.api.tools", "xref": {"fqname": "lanscape.blueprints.api..tools", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "lanscape.blueprints.api.tools", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "lanscape.blueprints.api.tools.test_subnet", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "lanscape.blueprints.api.tools.list_subnet", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["list all interface subets"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "lanscape.blueprints.api.port", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "lanscape.blueprints.api.port.get_port_lists", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Port Manager API", "#####